TITLE: Creating a Basic ReScript React Component
DESCRIPTION: A simple greeting component that demonstrates the basic structure of a ReScript React component. The component function is marked with @react.component and named 'make', returning JSX that renders a greeting message.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rescript-lang/rescript-lang.org.git/blob/master/pages/docs/react/v0.11.0/components-and-props.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: rescript
CODE:
```
// src/Greeting.res
@react.component
let make = () => {
  <div>
    {React.string("Hello ReScripters!")}
  </div>
}
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
import * as React from "react";

function Greeting(props) {
  return React.createElement("div", undefined, "Hello ReScripters!");
}

var make = Greeting;
```

