TITLE: Implementing a Counter Component with useState Hook in ReScript React
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates a Counter component that uses React.useState to maintain and update a count state when a button is clicked. It shows how to initialize state, update it with a setter function, and render the current count value in the UI.
