TITLE: Implementing a Recursive List Search Function in ReScript
DESCRIPTION: Shows a practical example of a recursive function that searches for an item in a list. The function returns true if the item is found, false otherwise.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rescript-lang/rescript-lang.org.git/blob/master/pages/docs/manual/v8.0.0/function.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_6

LANGUAGE: reason
CODE:
```
let rec listHas = (list, item) =>
  switch (list) {
  | [] => false
  | [a, ...rest] => a === item || listHas(rest, item)
  };
```

LANGUAGE: ml
CODE:
```
let rec listHas list item =
  match list with
  | [] -> false
  | a::rest -> (a == item) || (listHas rest item)
```

LANGUAGE: javascript
CODE:
```
function listHas(_list, item) {
  while(true) {
    var list = _list;
    if (!list) {
      return false;
    }
    if (list.hd === item) {
      return true;
    }
    _list = list.tl;
    continue ;
  };
}
```

