TITLE: Creating a Custom Set with PairComparator in ReasonML
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a custom comparator for pairs of integers and use it to initialize a set. The example shows creating a set and adding an element to it.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rescript-lang/rescript-lang.org.git/blob/master/pages/docs/manual/v8.0.0/api/belt/set.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: reasonml
CODE:
```
module PairComparator =
  Belt.Id.MakeComparable({
    type t = (int, int);
    let cmp = ((a0, a1), (b0, b1)) =>
      switch (Pervasives.compare(a0, b0)) {
      | 0 => Pervasives.compare(a1, b1)
      | c => c
      };
  });

let mySet = Belt.Set.make(~id=(module PairComparator));
let mySet2 = Belt.Set.add(mySet, (1, 2));
```

