TITLE: Finding Minimum Value in ReScript Belt.MutableSet
DESCRIPTION: The 'minimum' and 'minUndefined' functions return the minimum value in a MutableSet. 'minimum' returns an option type, while 'minUndefined' returns undefined for empty sets.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rescript-lang/rescript-lang.org.git/blob/master/pages/docs/manual/v8.0.0/api/belt/mutable-set.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_51

