TITLE: Replacing Substrings with Function in ReScript
DESCRIPTION: The unsafeReplaceBy0, unsafeReplaceBy1, unsafeReplaceBy2, and unsafeReplaceBy3 functions replace substrings in a string using a function to determine the replacement. They differ in the number of capturing groups in the regular expression.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rescript-lang/rescript-lang.org.git/blob/master/pages/docs/manual/v8.0.0/api/js/string-2.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_11

LANGUAGE: ReScript
CODE:
```
let unsafeReplaceBy0: (t, Js_re.t, (t, int, t) => t) => t;
let unsafeReplaceBy1: (t, Js_re.t, (t, t, int, t) => t) => t;
let unsafeReplaceBy2: (t, Js_re.t, (t, t, t, int, t) => t) => t;
let unsafeReplaceBy3: (t, Js_re.t, (t, t, t, t, int, t) => t) => t;
```

LANGUAGE: ReScript
CODE:
```
let str = "beautiful vowels";
let re = [%re "/[aeiou]/g"];
let matchFn = (matchPart, _offset, _wholeString) =>
  Js.String2.toUpperCase(matchPart);

Js.String2.unsafeReplaceBy0(str, re, matchFn)
  == "bEAUtIfUl vOwEls";

let str = "increment 23";
let re = [%re "/increment (\\d+)/g"];
let matchFn = (_matchPart, p1, _offset, wholeString) =>
  wholeString ++ " is " ++ Belt.Int.toString(int_of_string(p1) + 1);

Js.String2.unsafeReplaceBy1(str, re, matchFn)
  == "increment 23 is 24";

let str = "7 times 6";
let re = [%re "/(\\d+) times (\\d+)/"];
let matchFn = (matchPart, p1, p2, offset, wholeString) =>
  Belt.Int.toString(int_of_string(p1) * int_of_string(p2));

Js.String2.unsafeReplaceBy2(str, re, matchFn) == "42";
```

