TITLE: Breaking Out of a While Loop in ReScript
DESCRIPTION: Since ReScript doesn't have a break keyword, this example shows how to break out of a while loop using a mutable reference.
SOURCE: https://github.com/rescript-lang/rescript-lang.org.git/blob/master/pages/docs/manual/v11.0.0/control-flow.mdx#2025-04-18_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: res
CODE:
```
let break = ref(false)

while !break.contents {
  if Math.random() > 0.3 {
    break := true
  } else {
    Console.log("Still running")
  }
}
```

LANGUAGE: js
CODE:
```
var $$break = {
  contents: false
};

while(!$$break.contents) {
  if (Math.random() > 0.3) {
    $$break.contents = true;
  } else {
    console.log("Still running");
  }
};
```

